The paper discusses the algebraic approach to substructural logics, specifically Bunched Implications (BI) and Separation Logic (SL). This suggests that the paper may belong to the Logic (cs.LO) or Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper covers models arising from formal languages and semistructured data, which could fall under the Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-category. The paper also discusses decidability, which could place it in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper touches on tools and proof-theoretic presentations, which could suggest the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
